{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But previous to that, to go back some, the thing-- my, my mother, naturally, always insisted that I was a Jew and that I should believe again and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, frankly, to this day, I, I will never know why this woman was still religious after losing what I've counted-- there were what I could count, 80 members of her family, to include five kids.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It, it just was beyond me that she could believe in anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And me, with having been torn from the little Jewishness that I had, into Catholicism and being a devout Catholic for really almost four years and going to mass daily and praying, I could never, never understand nor accept why either God, if there were two or one God, whether it was Catholic or Jewish or whatever, could let that have happened to my family.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And by that time I had also learned about the 6 million Jews that had perished, 1 and 1/2 million children that had perished.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, how could any God-- one that I served, I thought, innocent children, innocent people-- how could it let that happen?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So instead of either turning to-- continuing to be a Catholic, because I was right on through liberation, or turning back to a Jewish, I became a devout atheist.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I could never, never, never understand again about religion.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I rejected it totally and completely.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, that hurt my mother a lot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that continued right on through, probably today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although today, maybe I won't call myself an atheist, maybe I'm a little agnostic right now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I still question and I still am certainly not a Jew any longer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's the part-- that is the difficult part today.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
